#note also YOUPONS available. Some really beautiful 8s in this rack too like DUOPSONY, UROSCOPY (which takes front O hook!), POLYPOUS and POROUSLY
>Akshay: DEILRTU E5 DILUT.R +32 43
#note I was amazed by how fast Akshay figured out that there were no 8s with his rack (I know he has an E from his opening phony).
>Jesse: GINRTUV D4 VIG +20 117
#note there are better scoring plays like VIRTU at 8A, but I wanted to force Akshay to have to battle back strategically, rather than just being able to get back in the game by drawing a bingo. VIG cuts his bingo percentage from 10% to 6% relative to LUV (which I actually didn't see). I would play LUV in hindsight and hope to pounce on any opening he makes.
>Akshay: ADEEELS 12C EASELED +77 120
>Jesse: ADENRTU B8 UNRATED +79 196
#note lucky to draw into a bingo in spite of not playing LUV and keeping a weaker leave. Also, this is definitely the best choice - UNRATED gives a much lower bingo % for Akshay next turn, about 11% vs 17% for NATURED. NATURED at 13H looks like a safer play because it doesn't open the TWS, but permanently forks the board for bingos (row 14 and right side).
